DbBufferPool
public abstract class BaseBufferPool<HeaderType extends PageHeader,PageType extends Page<HeaderType>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PageAccessor<HeaderType,PageType>

Manages the caching of pages in memory. A Buffer Pool manages the transfer of pages between disk and memory, and vice-versa. It also handles the caching policies used, with the objective of minimizing the number of disk operations. These policies include eviction strategies for removing pages from memory, and prefetching strategies, for pre-emptively reading pages from disk.
